<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Leading and half leading line heights leads to space above and below</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#line-height" />
        <meta name="flags" content="internal" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Line-height can be different from the content area so there is space above and below." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                width: 0;
                background: red;
            }
            #s1
            {
                background: red;
                color: red;
            }
            #s2
            {
                background-color: green;
                line-height: 0;
                font-size: 36pt;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the "FillerText" below does not extend beyond the green box and there is no red visible on the page.</p>
        <div id="d1">
            <div><span id="s1">FillerText</span></div>
            <div><span id="s2">FillerText</span></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>